---
import ContentPage from "../layouts/ContentPage.astro";
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";
import Prose from "../components/Prose.astro";

const title = "Persistent Memory for Claude Code — agentcairn";
const description =
  "Give Claude Code durable, local memory that survives every session — captured and recalled as Markdown you own. Install in one command.";
const cta = "cairn install claude-code";
---
<ContentPage title={title} description={description} cta={cta}>
  <Section id="intro">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-[40px] leading-tight mb-6">Persistent memory for Claude Code</h1>
    <Prose>
      <p>
        Claude Code starts every session cold. agentcairn gives it durable
        cross-session memory, stored as Markdown you own.
      </p>
    </Prose>
  </Section>

  <Section id="problem" eyebrow="The problem">
    <Prose>
      <p>
        Each new session begins from scratch. The decisions you made, the
        approaches you ruled out, the conventions you settled on — all of it is
        gone when the context window closes. You re-explain the same things, and
        the agent repeats mistakes it already learned to avoid.
      </p>
    </Prose>
  </Section>

  <Section id="how" eyebrow="How agentcairn works with Claude Code">
    <Prose>
      <p>
        Claude Code is a plugin host. The agentcairn plugin recalls relevant
        memory at the start of a session and captures at the end. It bundles an
        MCP server that exposes <code>recall</code>, <code>search</code>, and
        <code>remember</code>, so the agent can pull prior context or write a new
        fact on demand.
      </p>
      <p>
        Capture runs out-of-band. <code>cairn sweep</code> reads your session
        transcripts, redacts secrets, dedups, importance-gates, and distills what
        is worth keeping into the vault. Nothing blocks your work; the writing
        happens after the fact.
      </p>
      <p>Install it into Claude Code with one command:</p>
    </Prose>
    <pre class="font-mono text-[14px] mt-2 overflow-x-auto" tabindex="0"><code>cairn install claude-code</code></pre>
  </Section>

  <Section id="ownership" eyebrow="Your memory is yours">
    <Prose>
      <p>
        Memory is distilled into a local, Obsidian-compatible Markdown vault. It
        is the source of truth — not a one-way export from a database. The vault
        survives model upgrades, index rebuilds, and even uninstalling the tool.
        There is nothing to lose, because the truth was never trapped in a
        database.
      </p>
      <p>
        A rebuildable DuckDB index gives Claude Code fast hybrid retrieval
        (BM25 + vector + RRF, with an optional cross-encoder reranker). The index
        is a cache; the Markdown is the truth.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="/agent-memory" class="underline">What is agent memory?</a>
        &middot;
        <a href="/alternatives" class="underline">How agentcairn compares</a>
      </p>
    </Prose>
  </Section>
</ContentPage>
